{
  "texts": [
    "As we know, in precision and recall, there are false positive (FP) and false negative (FN), so F 1 -score also considers both of them.",
    "AUC provides an aggregate measure of the performance across all possible classification thresholds.",
    "The higher the accuracy, recall, F 1 -score, and AUC, the better the model's performance is at distinguishing between the positive and negative classes.",
    "(2) Accuracy = TP + TN TP + TN + FP + FN (3) Recall = TP TP + FN (4) Precision = TP TP + FP (5) F 1 -score = 2 × Recall × Precision Recall + PrecisionThe performance was evaluated on an independent test set, which included 256 patients with CHD.",
    "These test cases were also available on CHDmap when users created a new case."
  ]
}